The modern fashion of whitewashing the disreputable characters of history is one with which 1 have little sympathy, except so far as it must be admitted that no man is wholly bad, as no man is wholly good. Neither can I agree at all with those who would defend Tiberius by depreciating the motives of his historiari. That Tacitus sympathized with Germanicus and Agrippina, as against Tiberius, is no doubt tme; it was his , right as a patriot and an historian to choose his side.
